1
00:00:01,010 --> 00:00:03,100
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:05,770
Oh, no! Nirvana's started to move!

3
00:00:05,770 --> 00:00:08,600
Plus, Natsu and I are rockin' 
matching outfits for some reason.

4
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:09,650
I can hear you!

5
00:00:09,650 --> 00:00:13,820
Natsu can't handle transportation, 
so he can't even stand on it.

6
00:00:13,820 --> 00:00:14,820
I can hear you!

7
00:00:15,660 --> 00:00:17,620
I gotta do something to stop this thing!

8
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:19,120
I can hear you!

9
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:00,590
Huh? Look at that, Natsu!

10
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:04,770
See? The Magic Circle is back to normal.

11
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:07,510
I thought your last attack erased it...

12
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:12,310
Which means that unless we beat 
up Mr. Smarty Pants, it's no use.

13
00:02:13,750 --> 00:02:17,130
I can hear you! I won't let you.

14
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:19,800
Damn it, this guy's in our way.

15
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:22,870
We aren't going to lose 
when it comes to teamwork!

16
00:02:23,330 --> 00:02:26,070
Cobra, get rid of them.

17
00:02:26,070 --> 00:02:29,600
I hear ya. He'll make a 
nice meal for Cubellios.

18
00:02:31,290 --> 00:02:33,670
We aren't food!

19
00:02:33,670 --> 00:02:35,500
Bring it on!

20
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:40,840
Super Aerial Battle! Natsu vs. Cobra!

21
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:42,760
Cubellios!

22
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,640
Natsu!

23
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:52,020
Dazzling Blaze of the Fire Dragon!

24
00:02:54,290 --> 00:02:55,350
It missed?

25
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:57,820
No, I'm not through yet!

26
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:04,490
S-Seriously?

27
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:07,410
Natsu, you didn't hit him even once...

28
00:03:07,410 --> 00:03:11,910
But I threw so many... At least one 
should have hit him, normally...

29
00:03:11,910 --> 00:03:13,080
I wonder...

30
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:17,460
I told you already! Your 
attacks can't hit me.

31
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:20,070
I can hear your movements!

32
00:03:20,070 --> 00:03:24,180
Oh, you can, eh? Then take a listen to this!

33
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,020
Natsu, hang in there!

34
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:30,080
Fall!

35
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:33,980
Happy!

36
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:36,150
Aye, sir!

37
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:41,960
That was close... Nice one, Happy!

38
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:44,180
Where'd he go?

39
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:49,870
Run, run! It makes the 
hunt much more exciting!

40
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:52,660
Damn it... Really rubs our noses 
in his superiority, doesn't he?!

41
00:03:52,660 --> 00:03:56,940
I bet women totally hate the guy.

42
00:03:56,940 --> 00:03:58,330
Wait, hold it Happy.

43
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:01,880
Shh!

44
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,550
We'll hide here.

45
00:04:04,550 --> 00:04:06,340
Then do a surprise attack!

46
00:04:06,340 --> 00:04:07,220
Aye!

47
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,190
Don't say anything, Happy.

48
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,850
Aye.

49
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,400
He's here!

50
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,010
There you are!

51
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,330
Huh?

52
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:25,280
Not here.

53
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,530
But why?!

54
00:04:27,030 --> 00:04:28,740
I can <i>hear</i> you!

55
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:30,470
Damn it!

56
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:31,500
But why?

57
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:36,340
And what do you mean, 
women hate guys like me?

58
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,620
You heard <i>that</i>, too?

59
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:45,280
So, where are we?

60
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:49,260
It definitely looks like a city of some sort.

61
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:51,740
What kind of magic is this, anyway?

62
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:54,480
Some ruins with crazy huge legs?

63
00:04:54,780 --> 00:04:57,070
It seems like a really old city.

64
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,400
Exactly! Yes...

65
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:02,600
This is the fantastic city of Nirvana.

66
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:06,400
Seeing you here as well gives me confidence!

67
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,030
The dude from Lyon's guild!

68
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:10,340
And a member of Oracion Seis?!

69
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:11,660
But why?

70
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:14,990
Worry not. He has become our ally.

71
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:15,810
Huh?

72
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:18,450
Love, throughout the world! Yes...

73
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:19,960
No way!

74
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:23,370
Didn't this case keep 
spouting "money, money"?

75
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:26,880
Can the old dude use magic 
to make people see the light?

76
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:29,860
Well, this and that happened...

77
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:34,740
Oh yeah... Sherry went and flipped out, too.

78
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:41,190
Hate
Jewel

79
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:41,190
Love
Love

80
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:37,480
Good and evil swapped places, yeah.

81
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,400
What happened to Sherry?

82
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,190
Well, we already returned her to normal.

83
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:46,860
This is the ancient capital in which 
once lived the ancient Nirvit people.

84
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:47,570
Yes...

85
00:05:47,570 --> 00:05:49,180
The Nirvit?

86
00:05:49,470 --> 00:05:52,760
Correct. It was around 4000 years ago.

87
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:56,080
Many wars were happening 
around the world, see.

88
00:05:56,700 --> 00:06:01,160
The Nirvit maintained their neutrality, 
and lamented the state of the world.

89
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:05,870
So they created a magic that would 
restore balance to the world. Yes...

90
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:08,760
You don't mean that magic is...

91
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:13,820
Yes. An ultra-magic that 
swaps light and darkness.

92
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:19,260
That magic was given the name of 
the Kingdom of Peace, Nirvana.

93
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:20,410
Yes...

94
00:06:20,410 --> 00:06:22,210
So this walking city...

95
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:24,360
...is Nirvana itself!

96
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:29,480
Ironic... Sheesh.

97
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:37,120
It has the name that signifies peace, 
and yet is being used for evil.

98
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:40,310
It <i>would've</i> been a good magic,

99
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:44,210
if they hadn't originally used turning 
light into darkness as one of its elements.

100
00:06:44,210 --> 00:06:50,550
Nothing can be done now. The ancients 
likely never considered so far ahead.

101
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:55,180
Strong magic has strong secondary effects.

102
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:05,540
In any case, we are in trouble 
now that it is moving.

103
00:07:05,540 --> 00:07:08,440
We must stop it without any further delay.

104
00:07:08,730 --> 00:07:09,790
Yes...

105
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:11,130
Well, duh!

106
00:07:11,130 --> 00:07:11,760
Yup!

107
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:19,130
What?

108
00:07:19,130 --> 00:07:20,390
A light!

109
00:07:20,390 --> 00:07:22,250
That's Brain, yes...

110
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:27,940
He is probably moving this city 
from atop the King's Summit.

111
00:07:27,940 --> 00:07:31,420
While he is doing that, Brain 
cannot use other magic.

112
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,740
It is our chance to strike!

113
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:34,680
Yes...

114
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,930
If he's moving it... Then 
is he heading somewhere?

115
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:39,560
Perhaps...

116
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:43,230
However, I do not know where to.

117
00:07:43,890 --> 00:07:44,970
Yes.

118
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:50,490
Only I understand what Father is thinking.

119
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:53,860
Midnight.

120
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:55,600
Oracion Seis!

121
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,300
It's the one that was always asleep!

122
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:01,870
Hot Eye... You betrayed my father?

123
00:08:01,870 --> 00:08:03,400
No, I did not.

124
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:07,500
I merely realized that Brain is wrong.

125
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,590
What?

126
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:12,000
You say my father is wrong?

127
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,310
When did he...

128
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:16,430
Wait, what do you mean, "father"?

129
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,560
It's a father-son Dark Guild?

130
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:23,540
People's hearts are not meant 
to be twisted around by magic.

131
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:27,980
Even those with weak hearts, 
we can raise to become strong!

132
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:43,790
What just happened?

133
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:46,650
Hot Eye-dono caused the ground to collapse!

134
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,430
He saved us!

135
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:52,880
You all should go to the King's Summit.

136
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:59,010
The Six General's strength is well 
matched. Leave Midnight to me.

137
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,140
You and I, fight?

138
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:04,330
Liquid Ground!

139
00:09:08,810 --> 00:09:12,180
Oracion Seis are gonna crush each other?

140
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:15,250
This is really quite the development.

141
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:16,530
Hot Eye-dono...

142
00:09:16,530 --> 00:09:19,160
Now, hurry and go!

143
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,580
And also...

144
00:09:20,930 --> 00:09:25,500
My real name is... Richard! Yes...

145
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,900
Richard-dono...

146
00:09:31,690 --> 00:09:33,940
Telling your real name to the enemy...

147
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:37,630
You really have fallen, Hot Eye.

148
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:41,720
I have been awakened by love! 
I have no need for codenames!

149
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:42,470
Prepare yourself!

150
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,180
He dodged again!

151
00:09:48,180 --> 00:09:50,690
You never learn, do you?

152
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:54,410
Damn it! Nothing I've thrown at him connects!

153
00:09:54,410 --> 00:09:57,650
I wonder if he has some magic 
that lets him read our movements?

154
00:09:57,650 --> 00:10:00,140
No, it lets me <i>hear</i> them!

155
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:06,040
I can hear your mind's thoughts, 
and tell your movements.

156
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:09,810
My thoughts?

157
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:10,830
In that case...

158
00:10:10,830 --> 00:10:12,880
Can you hear this?

159
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:22,390
I'm well aware that you like fish.

160
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:24,330
He can really hear them!

161
00:10:24,330 --> 00:10:27,190
I cleared my mind of 
everything except for fish!

162
00:10:27,930 --> 00:10:29,070
Ooh! Me next!

163
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:30,350
He's totally spot on!

164
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:32,580
They think my magic's some sideshow?

165
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:48,830
Damn it... That was a pretty 
funny one, I'll admit it.

166
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:50,310
All right, I killed!

167
00:10:50,310 --> 00:10:52,220
But yeah, he can totally hear them.

168
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:54,650
What were you thinking?

169
00:10:54,650 --> 00:10:55,920
I'm really curious.

170
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:58,100
I'll tell you later.

171
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:00,110
But this is gonna be tricky...

172
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:04,260
I have a good idea, but 
I think he can hear it.

173
00:11:05,020 --> 00:11:08,700
Think "right" but attack from the left.

174
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:11,340
Not going to work.

175
00:11:11,630 --> 00:11:14,940
I can hear you planning it out.

176
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,980
You punks have no way to win.

177
00:11:19,350 --> 00:11:21,320
Oh, I see.

178
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:25,530
I hear you.  You thought about quite a lot.

179
00:11:25,530 --> 00:11:29,410
You have three or four decent plans.

180
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:30,540
I heard them all!

181
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:32,600
That is <i>so</i> cheating!

182
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,040
I guess we got no choice 
but to head straight in!

183
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:35,980
Aye, sir!

184
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:37,300
Plan C!

185
00:11:37,300 --> 00:11:39,530
Charge!

186
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,760
Right hook.

187
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:43,390
Left kick.

188
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:48,220
Followed by a right roundhouse kick, 
and a comeback straight right!

189
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,640
What? Impossible...

190
00:12:02,110 --> 00:12:06,810
I can hear it... He's... 
not thinking anything!

191
00:12:08,950 --> 00:12:11,210
I don't know whether he's stupid or a genius!

192
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:13,370
But I never faced someone like him before.

193
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,880
I see. Little tricks ain't 
working for you, eh?

194
00:12:20,190 --> 00:12:21,830
M-My hand...

195
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:23,260
Natsu, what's the matter?

196
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:30,090
Poison Dragon Cobra... 
It's time I got serious.

197
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,430
N-No way...

198
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:34,300
Is this guy a...

199
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:36,530
...Dragon Slayer?

200
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,660
Are you okay?

201
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:08,480
Damn it... What's with these attacks?

202
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:10,470
Each time they hit, I get more numb!

203
00:13:10,470 --> 00:13:13,350
I can hear your pain!

204
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:19,010
The attacks of a poison dragon 
can infect and destroy anything!

205
00:13:19,010 --> 00:13:23,360
Is that so? I'll just burn 
that poison right up!

206
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,430
Let's go!

207
00:13:24,430 --> 00:13:25,510
Aye, sir!

208
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:28,150
Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!

209
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:29,630
Fall and rot!

210
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:31,410
Fang Thrust of the Poison Dragon!

211
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:46,670
Oops! I dropped 'im!

212
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:51,520
You're nauseous already? 
That was quick, Natsu.

213
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,710
Come on, snap out of it.

214
00:13:53,710 --> 00:13:55,460
I'm sorry I dropped you.

215
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:58,380
I-I'm fine...

216
00:13:59,230 --> 00:14:03,160
He don't know when to quit, do he, Cubellios?

217
00:14:04,230 --> 00:14:05,720
Say that again!

218
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,440
Yeah!

219
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,820
Time to kick ass!

220
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:11,530
I can hear everything...

221
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:15,740
Not just your thoughts, but the movement 
of your muscles, even your breathing!

222
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:16,920
Crap!

223
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:20,330
Our attacks aren't hitting again!

224
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,790
Weren't you not thinking?

225
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:27,600
Ever since I realized he was a dragon 
slayer, it hasn't gone so well...

226
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,880
Are you saying he's gotten to you?

227
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:32,650
Come on, clear your mind!

228
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:36,330
Thinking isn't like you, Natsu! Don't do it!

229
00:14:36,330 --> 00:14:38,090
What's that supposed to mean, damn you?

230
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:39,600
You makin' fun of me?

231
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:41,100
No!

232
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:44,280
I said that you work better 
when you don't think!

233
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,910
Don't. Think.

234
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:47,140
You don't have to say it twice!

235
00:14:47,140 --> 00:14:49,930
And you're makin' fun of me, damn it!

236
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:51,350
No, I'm not!

237
00:14:51,350 --> 00:14:52,550
...I think.

238
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:54,000
What do you mean "I think..."?

239
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,820
You totally made fun of me!

240
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:59,190
Anyway, just concentrate on Cobra!

241
00:14:59,190 --> 00:14:59,880
Here we go!

242
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:01,210
Aye, sir!

243
00:15:02,190 --> 00:15:04,630
Talons of the Fire Dragon!

244
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:06,920
Spiral Jaw of the Poison Dragon!

245
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:21,080
This is no time to get queasy!

246
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,860
Natsu!

247
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:32,200
An explosion?

248
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:34,280
Somebody is fighting!

249
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:35,990
That's pretty impressive...

250
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:37,400
Which means it's...

251
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,270
...Natsu, right? Definitely!

252
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,450
Yup!

253
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,160
Did he turn to ash?

254
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:47,090
No, something's strange... 
What is this sound?

255
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:53,790
He's eating the flames?

256
00:15:53,790 --> 00:15:56,530
Well, don't see that every day, Cubellios.

257
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:03,350
Now that I've eaten, I'm all  revved up!

258
00:16:03,350 --> 00:16:08,830
Sure, you might have eaten flames to 
recover, but that doesn't mean I can't hear you!

259
00:16:08,830 --> 00:16:11,060
Keep on blabbing!

260
00:16:11,060 --> 00:16:11,940
Here!

261
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:14,150
Follow me if you dare, slanty-eyes!

262
00:16:14,150 --> 00:16:16,640
Hey, you look just like me!

263
00:16:17,490 --> 00:16:19,630
Scales of the Poison Dragon!

264
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:22,610
Max Speed!

265
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:37,890
Stupid... Don't you realize a 
feint isn't going to work by now?

266
00:16:37,890 --> 00:16:40,220
Is this all you got after 
eating those flames?

267
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:42,430
I had to get close!

268
00:16:42,690 --> 00:16:44,270
Roar of the...

269
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:48,900
Natsu!

270
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:51,740
You're overdoing it!

271
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,790
Well, I didn't know 'til I tried...

272
00:16:53,790 --> 00:16:55,110
You're overdoing it!

273
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:56,610
I said you don't have to say things twice!

274
00:16:56,610 --> 00:16:59,170
Now it's my turn to eat!

275
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,280
Poison gas...

276
00:17:10,350 --> 00:17:12,240
He's eating the poison.

277
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:14,170
That doesn't look so healthy.

278
00:17:15,370 --> 00:17:18,260
Now that I've eaten, I'm 
all revved up... yeah?

279
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:19,640
Don't copy me!

280
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,970
Rot and die!

281
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:23,740
Roar of the...

282
00:17:23,740 --> 00:17:24,850
His breath attack?

283
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:25,980
This is bad!

284
00:17:25,980 --> 00:17:27,800
...Poison Dragon!

285
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:39,020
W-What? That didn't cause 
much damage at all...

286
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:42,830
What's wrong, Happy?

287
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:46,030
Hang in there, Happy!

288
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,010
Hey!

289
00:17:47,010 --> 00:17:52,960
For some reason... my body... 
isn't moving right...

290
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,320
Don't worry about it! Same for me.

291
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,760
That's exactly what I'm worried about!

292
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:03,450
The breath of the Poison Dragon infects 
your entire body with a virus!

293
00:18:03,450 --> 00:18:07,230
It slowly steals your 
mobility and then your life!

294
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:14,630
The moment you got hit with that 
breath, your defeat was guaranteed!

295
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:18,050
Oh, shut the hell up!

296
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:22,490
Don't worry 'bout no poison, Happy!

297
00:18:22,490 --> 00:18:23,870
Aye, sir!

298
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:26,750
Does he ever listen to people 
when they're talking?

299
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:30,000
Wing Slash of the Fire Dragon!

300
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:38,870
I can hear your movements!

301
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,540
Damn it!

302
00:18:40,540 --> 00:18:42,650
Natsu, don't think!

303
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:45,180
Whatever! You concentrate on flying!

304
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:48,400
I am! All I'm thinking about is flying!

305
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,650
You big liar!

306
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:53,610
These guys are so annoying, 
don't you think, Cubellios?

307
00:18:55,900 --> 00:19:00,400
But for someone to be able to still 
move after being hit with my poison...

308
00:19:00,670 --> 00:19:04,450
You Old Generation Dragon 
Slayers ain't half bad.

309
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:06,050
Old Generation?

310
00:19:06,050 --> 00:19:08,430
I'm a New Generation Dragon Slayer.

311
00:19:08,430 --> 00:19:15,290
I received the power to slay dragons by 
having dragon lacrima infused into my body.

312
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:17,480
It's what Gramps said.

313
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:19,170
He's the same as Laxus!

314
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:22,130
He's not a real Dragon Slayer!

315
00:19:22,130 --> 00:19:23,710
Real?

316
00:19:23,710 --> 00:19:27,830
Dragon slaying magic was originally 
only able to be learned by dragons!

317
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:30,510
It was not a technique for humans.

318
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:34,080
If you ask me, you're the 
one that's the freak!

319
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:37,230
Because there ain't any 
dragons in this world!

320
00:19:37,230 --> 00:19:38,730
What did you say?!

321
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:41,610
Try sayin' that again!

322
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:43,700
There's Igneel, damn it!

323
00:19:44,490 --> 00:19:46,190
No, there isn't!

324
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,990
Dragons are extinct!

325
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,990
Don't go killing them off so easy!

326
00:19:50,990 --> 00:19:53,090
Fangs of the Poison Dragon!

327
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:56,930
Natsu, hang in there!

328
00:19:57,380 --> 00:20:00,680
M-My body... I can't move...

329
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,340
Damn it...

330
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:06,180
I can hear the poison spreading 
through your entire body.

331
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:10,530
Rot and die right here 
before me, Old Generation.

332
00:20:10,530 --> 00:20:15,230
Natsu... I'm at my limit, too...

333
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:19,330
Happy, drop me right on top of him.

334
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:24,450
What are you saying, Natsu? Didn't 
you just say you couldn't move?

335
00:20:24,850 --> 00:20:27,750
That's why I have to 
finish it with this move.

336
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:29,670
What are you going to do?

337
00:20:29,670 --> 00:20:32,130
A full power Roar of the Fire Dragon?

338
00:20:32,130 --> 00:20:35,750
Idiot... I can hear what you're thinking.

339
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,520
Happy, now!

340
00:20:37,520 --> 00:20:38,710
Aye!

341
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:42,350
It was more of a nuisance when he 
was attacking without thinking.

342
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,040
This is over!

343
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:45,690
Roar of the...

344
00:20:45,690 --> 00:20:47,760
It's no use. I can hear you!

345
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,910
You plan on aiming all around!

346
00:20:49,910 --> 00:20:51,640
Think you can hit me no matter where I dodge?

347
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:57,060
But! It won't reach 
straight behind your head!

348
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,810
I'll smash in that head of yours!

349
00:20:59,810 --> 00:21:01,400
Natsu!

350
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:04,520
Go meet your dragons in the afterlife!

351
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:10,180
Damn you!

352
00:21:33,770 --> 00:21:36,860
What is that noise?  A roar?

353
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:38,580
Some kind of giant monster?

354
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:40,540
No... That's...

355
00:21:47,450 --> 00:21:50,410
My ears!

356
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:01,850
That was some roar, all right...

357
00:22:03,180 --> 00:22:06,260
Well, I figured he had 
such good hearing that...

358
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:09,200
Just like I planned, yup!

359
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,970
It was a total coincidence, though.

360
00:22:10,970 --> 00:22:15,660
Impossible... Defeating Cobra 
with nothing but a scream?

361
00:22:15,970 --> 00:22:19,230
What in the world is that man?

362
00:23:55,700 --> 00:24:00,390
That big dude from Lamia Scale said he 
was one of the 10 Wizard Saints, right?

363
00:24:00,390 --> 00:24:03,590
Yeah. I bet he's super strong!

364
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:05,700
Don't look like it to me.

365
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:06,820
In his face, anyway.

366
00:24:06,820 --> 00:24:08,790
What does the face have to do with it?

367
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,670
Well, maybe I'll fight him later!

368
00:24:10,670 --> 00:24:13,470
I bet that you'll lose, Natsu!

369
00:24:13,930 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Jura, the Tenth Saint!

370
00:24:16,820 --> 00:24:19,010
Why won't you bet that I win?

371
00:24:19,010 --> 00:24:20,650
You're cold, Happy!

372
00:24:20,650 --> 00:24:23,850
I make it a rule not to 
fight a losing battle.

373
00:24:24,120 --> 00:24:26,350


